The line item related to interest accrued but not yet received is typically named "Interest Receivable."

From the balance sheet section of the problem:

- Initial value (2023-12-31) of Interest Receivable: 0.00
- End value (2024-01-29) of Interest Receivable: 10051.66

This matches with the value of "Interest Income" in the income statement (10051.66) and the "(Increase) Decrease in Interest Receivable" in the cash flow statement (-10051.66), confirming that this is the accrued interest not yet received.

Hence, the initial and final values are:

- Initial value: 0.00  
- End value: 10051.66
